# Next.js 16 Productivity App - Coding Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- Prisma + PostgreSQL
- NextAuth.js

## CRITICAL RULES (Follow Strictly)
- **NO explanatory comments** - Code must be self-documenting
- **NO inline comments** explaining what code does
- **NO function/method comments** above implementations
- **NO code block comments** - Use descriptive variable/function names

## Code Style
- Named exports only (no defaults)
- Absolute imports with `@/` prefix
- Functional components with hooks
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any`

## Architecture
- Server Components by default
- Server Actions for mutations
- Feature-based organization
- Clean separation of concerns
